MLB All-Star game is a joke.<br>
<br>
1.  Fans should not vote..Period.  Voting should be done by players and coaches - No media either.  The average fan has no idea who is having a good year on other teams outside their division and especially not in the other league.  They vote based by biasm and historical data.  If this means that the fans don't get to see Griffey, Giambi, Sosa, etc every damn year, then so be it.  It is a game for the players who are playing better THAT YEAR than anyone else in their positions.<br>
<br>
<br>
2.  IF you let the fans vote, then by god lose the World Series Home Field Advantage Rule that they added this year.  How incredibly stupid is this.  An American League team who wins 115 games and cruises through the playoffs into the World Series could lose Home Field Advantage to the National League team (even though they only won 95 games) because the National league won the All-Star game.  Honestly, could anything be more unfair than that.  What team of monkies did they have working on this one.<br>
