<br>
I think they should do that again. Hold one in a NL city and another in an AL city (and if its New York or Chicago that have a team in each league, don't let them have both games, or have one a year and a second the next). <br>
<br>
Have the first one like they do now, at the mid-point of the season, and have the fans vote on it like now. My only gripe is that I don't like the fact that the managers pick the pitchers, since they tend to pick half their own pitching staff. I think they should at least make a rule that you can only have one pitcher from your own team. Period. Not one starter, one closer, and one reliever. (If I had my way, though, all Braves and Yankees pitchers would be banned from the line-ups, since they've hogged the spots too many times over the last decade)<br>
<br>
For the second game, hold it right after the last game of the World Series and have it be based purely on stats (post-season not counting), but don't let anyone from the two World Series teams be in the game, except maybe the MVP for each team (but only if they have the stats, not just because they were an MVP for the Series). If a player was in the first All-Star game due to fan voting but qualifies, skip him and go to the next best player and flip a coin or something if there's a tie. There should also be a rule for both All-Star games that you have to have one player from each team and a limit to how many players you can have from each team, so you don't have five guys from one team out there. (Yes, even the Detroit Tigers, who quite frankly could probably lose an exhibition game to a high school team nowadays, should have a player in the game - Detriot used to be one of my favorite teams, so don't crack on me if you're a Tigers fan. I'm just calling it like I see it.)<br>
<br>
I'm just glad they expanded the rosters by two pitchers so we can't have a fiasco like last year's game. If the managers still somehow go through all their pitchers like they did last year, then THEY should be forced to get out there and throw the ball until the game ends!<br>
